                "url": "/topics/measuring"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/hajoon_chang_694436",
        "quote": "Markets are, in the end, man-made devices for utilitarian purposes, not a force of nature that we should not try to resist. If they end up serving the interests of only a tiny minority, as is increasingly the case, we have the right - and indeed the duty - to regulate them in the interest of greater social good.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ha-Joon Chang",
            "url": "/quotes/hajoon_chang_694436"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Good",
                "url": "/topics/good"
