                "url": "/topics/assess"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tend",
                "url": "/topics/tend"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/hajoon_chang_694438",
        "quote": "Patent monopoly creates a lot of problems. It allows the patentee to charge the maximum to consumers. This may not be a problem if the patented product is a luxury item, like parts that go into a smartphone, but can violate basic human rights if it involves things such as life-saving drugs.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Ha-Joon Chang",
            "url": "/quotes/hajoon_chang_694438"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Life-Saving",
